[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{NORTH realizes SOUTH has fewer than 8 points, but the 3\S support bid is enough 
for her to try a RKCB 4NT bid.

SOUTH shows two Key Cards and NORTH figures they will be the \SK and one of the 
red Aces. So she bids 6\S. If instead the Key Cards are the two red Aces NORTH 
might possibly make all thirteen tricks with a finesse.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "2"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "NS"]
[Deal "E:KQJ5.AK652.6.AKQ T93.T3.KT432.T75 A72.Q74.985.9843 864.J98.AQJ7.J62"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "6H"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2C pass 2D pass 2H pass 3H pass 4NT pass 5C pass 5D pass 6H pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 2, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "advanced"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/roman_key_card"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST's 3\H bid is "encouraging" so EAST bids 4NT.

When WEST shows one Key Card, (an Ace), EAST is afraid he may have a trump loser as well the 
other Ace. To find out about the \HQ he 
bids 5\D, the Queen Ask.

WEST has the \HQ but no King so she jumps 
to 6\H.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "S"]
[Vulnerable "None"]
[Deal "S:KQJ5.AK652.6.AKQ T98.T.KQ942.T975 A72.J9874.85.843 643.Q3.AJT73.J62"]
